cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.NE, cs.DS

The paper discusses the convergence rates of TD(0) algorithm, which is a commonly used algorithm in reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also uses stochastic approximation techniques, which are commonly used in neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a likely sub-category as well. Finally, the paper deals with convergence rates and analysis, which falls under the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
